<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="K_4610" type="Brief"><teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>Trevenen James Holland an Alfred Escher, London, Freitag, 01. März 1872</title></titleStmt><publicationStmt><p>Digitale Briefedition Alfred Escher, Zürich: Alfred Escher-Stiftung.</p></publicationStmt><sourceDesc><msDesc><msIdentifier><institution>SBB Historic</institution><idno>VGB_GB_SBBGB03_001</idno></msIdentifier></msDesc><bibl type="printed"/></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><textClass><keywords scheme="http://briefedition.alfred-escher.ch/keywords"><term>Tunnelbau</term><term>Bewerbungen/Empfehlungen/Referenzen</term><term>Eisenbahngesellschaften Offerten</term></keywords></textClass><correspDesc><correspAction type="sent"><persName key="Holland Trevenen James" type="addressee">Trevenen James Holland</persName><persName key="Escher (vom Glas) Alfred" type="sender">Alfred Escher</persName><placeName>London</placeName><date when="1872-03-01">01. März 1872</date></correspAction><correspAction type="received"><placeName>Bern</placeName></correspAction><correspContext><ref type="previous" target="B2601"/><ref type="next" target="B7710"/><ref type="next-in-corresp" target="B7793"/></correspContext></correspDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text><front>
      
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_4610_p1"> <note type="addendum" xml:id="K_4610_c0">Nachträgliche Notiz oben links von Eschers Hand mit Bleistift: <orig><add type="?">8/4</add></orig>.</note> <lb xml:id="p1-l1"/>
          <hi rend="printed">THE PATENT <lb xml:id="p1-l2"/>
			TUNNELING<lb xml:id="p1-l3"/>
			&amp; MINING MACHINE<lb xml:id="p1-l4"/>
			COMPANY<lb xml:id="p1-l5"/>
			LIMITED</hi>
        </p>
      
      <div type="dateline">
        <p rend="right" xml:id="K_4610_p2"><lb xml:id="p1-l6"/>5, Great Winchester <choice><abbr>St.</abbr><expan>Street (Strasse)</expan></choice> Buildings<lb xml:id="p1-l7"/><hi rend="printed"><del>8, Old Jewry</del> <placeName key="London (UK)">London</placeName> <choice><abbr>E. C.</abbr><expan>Eastern Central (östlicher Stadtteil)</expan></choice> </hi></p>
        <p rend="right" xml:id="K_4610_p3"><lb xml:id="p1-l8"/>
          <date when="1872-03-01">
            <choice><abbr>1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> </abbr><expan>first (erstens)</expan></choice> March <hi rend="printed">
					18<del>6</del> </hi>72</date>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div type="opener">
        <p rend="center" xml:id="K_4610_p4"><lb xml:id="p1-l9"/> To the Chairman of the<lb xml:id="p1-l10"/>
          <choice><abbr>St.</abbr><expan>Sankt / Sanct / Saint (heilig)</expan></choice> Gothard
					Railway Company
					<lb xml:id="p1-l11"/><placeName key="Bern (Stadt)">Berne</placeName> </p>
      </div>
      <div type="opener">
        <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_4610_p5"><lb xml:id="p1-l12"/> Sir</p>
      </div>
    </front><body>
      <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_4610_p6"><lb xml:id="p1-l13"/> Having been informed that you are<lb xml:id="p1-l14"/> about to commence the <placeName key="St. Gotthard (Pass)">St.
				Gothard</placeName> Tunnel,<lb xml:id="p1-l15"/> I beg to forward for the information of your<lb xml:id="p1-l16"/> Board a
				printed extract from the report of<lb xml:id="p1-l17"/> The <persName key="Larcy Charles de">Minister of Public Works</persName> of <placeName key="Frankreich">France</placeName> <lb xml:id="p1-l18"/>
				relating to our rock-boring machine; and I<lb xml:id="p1-l19"/> beg to intimate that my Company is
				prepared<lb xml:id="p1-l20"/> to enter into negotiations with you for driving<lb xml:id="p1-l21"/> the heading of
				any tunnels required. </p>
      <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_4610_p7"><lb xml:id="p1-l22"/> Captain <persName key="Penrice Herbert Newton">Penrice</persName>, late Royal Engineers, the<lb xml:id="p1-l23"/> Patentee and
				consulting engineer of this Company,<lb xml:id="p1-l24"/> will be at <placeName key="Bern (Stadt)">Berne</placeName> shortly, and, on my
				hearing<lb xml:id="p1-l25"/> from you regarding this matter, I shall be<lb xml:id="p1-l26"/> happy to ask him to
				call on you to give you<lb xml:id="p1-l27"/> any further information you require. </p>
    </body><back>
      <div type="closer">
        <p rend="center" xml:id="K_4610_p8"><lb xml:id="p1-l28"/> I am, Dear Sir<lb xml:id="p1-l29"/> Yours very truly
				</p>
      </div>
      <div type="signature">
        <p rend="center" xml:id="K_4610_p9"><lb xml:id="p1-l30"/>
					 Major <lb xml:id="p1-l31"/> Chairman </p>
      </div>
    </back></text></TEI>